    "where V 0 is the total flux density of the Gaussian source, |u| is the length of the baseline, and θ is its FWHM in radians.",
    "The intermediate-to-long baselines tend to measure larger correlated flux density than what is expected for an equivalent Gaussian source.",
    "We can deduce that the measured amplitude ratio of the ALMA-LMT over SMT-LMT baselines will be larger than the corresponding ratio from a circular Gaussian source model.",
    "Consequently, the FWHM size of a circular Gaussian determined by the amplitude ratio between SMT-LMT and ALMA-LMT baselines provides an estimate of the minimum compact source size θ cpct that is not significantly affected by the intrinsic fine-scale source structure:",
